    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of shrub or small tree found in regions of Africa, the Americas, southern Asia, and Australasia. extremely tough and durable. In New Zealand its heavy wood is traditionally used by the Maori for making weapons, ax handles, walking sticks, and for other purposes.</Note_Text>
